    <note>She Congruan [14230] According to Li(2) Zhiyi's [3484] funerary inscription for his descendant, Keshi [14250] (q.v.), from the Later Wei (or Northern Wei), the Zhe(1) were a great lineage (dazu), who were a hereditary skilled military lineage of this region. This is the lineage that provided the hereditary prefects of Fuzhou on the Shanxi-Inner Mongolian border. Congruan was military governor of Binning. See documentation for son, Deyi [14231].</note>
